  "response": "Different animals perceive humans in various ways, often based on their own experiences and interactions:\n\n1. Dogs often see humans as pack leaders or companions\n\n2. Cats may view humans as large, strange cats or providers of food and shelter\n\n3. Prey animals like deer or rabbits typically see humans as potential predators\n\n4. Some primates recognize humans as distinct but potentially social creatures\n\n5. Domesticated animals often see humans as sources of food, protection, and care\n\nThe exact perceptions vary by species, individual animal experiences, and their cognitive capabilities.",
